***Solution 1* - Split linked list**

---
suppose we have two linkedList :
>`l1 =  1 -> 2 -> 3`
>` l2 =  4 -> 5 -> 6` ,
> **l2rev** = ` 6 -> 5  -> 4 `

* Now if  we have to merge **l1** and **l2rev** then this question is going to bit more simpler right
	**Now how do we merge :**
		**p1 =  l1**
		**p2 =  l2rev**
	* p1 is always point to node whose next is going to fill 
	* p2 point to to node which is going to fill in **p1 next**

**So steps involve are :**
* split linkedlist into two halves
	* find mid and split
	* and revese second half
* merge these two halves

### Lets Code this Approch 👩🏻‍💻 💻
---
```
class Solution {
    public ListNode midNode(ListNode head){
        ListNode fast =  head, slow  =  head;
        while(fast.next!=null && fast.next.next!=null){
            fast =  fast.next.next;
            slow =  slow.next;
        }
        return slow;
    }

    public ListNode reverse(ListNode head){
        ListNode curr =  head, prev=  null, next = null;
        while(curr!=null){
            next  =  curr.next;
            curr.next =  prev ;
            prev =  curr;
            curr  =  next;
        }
        return prev;
    }


    public void reorderList(ListNode head) {

        ListNode midNode =  midNode(head);
        ListNode nextToMid =  midNode.next;
        midNode.next = null;
        ListNode p2 =  reverse(nextToMid);

        ListNode p1 =  head ,p1Next;    
        while(p1!=null && p2!=null){
            p1Next =  p1.next;                                    
			p1.next =  p2;

            p1 =  p2;
            p2=p1Next;                        
        }                
    }            
}
```


---

TIME COMPLEXITY : **O(n)**
SPACE COMPLEXITY : **O(1)**


