The first solution, it's a normal one, and I think it's more in line with the requirements "NOT modify the node". Here is the algorithm:

1. Traversal the linked list to find the middle node
2. Reverse the latter half
3. Reorder the whole linked list

```js
const reorderList = head => {
  if (!head || !head.next || !head.next.next) return head;

  let slow = head;
  let fast = head.next;
  while (fast && fast.next) {
    slow = slow.next;
    fast = fast.next.next;
